      "dimensions": 1,
      "description": "fill - The input is stretched/squashed to fill the resolution and aspect ratio specified on the Common page. fithorz - The input is uniformly scaled to fit horizontally. fitvert - The input is uniformly scaled to fit vertically. fitbest - The input is uniformly scaled to fit using the best possible match that does not crop any of the input. It's a \"fit inside\". The aspect ratio of the input is maintained. fitoutside - This is the opposite of Fit Best. It is uniformly scaled so the input covers the specified resolution completely. nativeres - The input is not scaled. If the specified resolution is smaller than the input, it is cropped.",
      "tooltip": "",
